                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you work primarily off a laptop, you’re likely already aware of the productivity and comfort benefits that a few small gadgets can provide. The best part is that many of them can make a meaningful difference without draining your wallet.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 19:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/affordable-laptop-workspace-upgrades-under-20/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Hate the Windows 11 Widgets Panel? Here's How to Completely Get Rid of It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hate-the-windows-11-widgets-panel-heres-how-to-completely-get-rid-of-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/windows_11_widgets3-1.png" length="2598" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Until Microsoft improves the widget panel, you can disable it completely.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The widgets panel on Windows 11 gives you quick access to information like news, weather, stocks, and more. However, I really don't like it, as it takes up a good amount of taskbar space and often interferes with my workflow by popping up unexpectedly. If you also don't find the widgets panel helpful, here's how you can disable it completely.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hate-the-windows-11-widgets-panel-heres-how-to-completely-get-rid-of-it/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Disabled Windows Startup Apps—Here's How Much Faster My PC Boots]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/disabling-startup-apps-improve-boot-time/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/the-windows-10-startup-screen-in-the-settings-app.jpg" length="145" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hardware]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Minor tweak, major payoff!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If your device takes ages to boot, and you blame it on its age, you’re mistaken. I used to think the same until I found the real culprit—too many apps loading at startup. Turning off unnecessary apps made my device boot faster. I applied this change on two devices, and here’s the difference it made.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 18:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/disabling-startup-apps-improve-boot-time/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Hybrid Became the Benchmark for Longevity]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-hybrid-became-the-benchmark-for-longevity/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/toyota-prius-2012-hd-d90892a01bb68286b64d76c90f129020612fedb89.jpg" length="285" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hybrid Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[Toyota]]></category><description><![CDATA[
